[assistant] Fixed the test cleanup issue.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Problem:
[assistant] - `channel.close().syncUninterruptibly()` requires the Netty channel to be registered with an event loop.
[assistant] - The test only needs the public config path, so event-loop registration is unnecessary.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Change:
[assistant] - Open a JDK `DatagramChannel` directly.
[assistant] - Construct `NioDatagramChannel` from it.
[assistant] - Close the JDK channel directly in `finally`.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Updated file:
[assistant] - `tests/src/io.netty/netty-all/4.0.23.Final/src/test/java/io_netty/netty_all/NioDatagramChannelConfigTest.java`
[assistant] 
[assistant] I did not run tests locally, per the original instruction.
[assistant] 
